<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc337c4ff-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053"><num value="2053">§ 2053.</num><heading> Default</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idc337c500-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> The Secretary shall take such steps as may be necessary to obtain repayment on any loan that is in default and that is guaranteed under this subchapter.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idc337c501-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><chapeau> Upon default of a loan guaranteed under this subchapter and terminated pursuant to State law, a lender may file a claim under the guarantee for an amount not to exceed the lesser of—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc337c502-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the maximum guarantee; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc337c503-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><chapeau> the difference between—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idc337c504-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053/b/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> the total outstanding obligation on the loan, including principal, interest, and expenses authorized by the loan documents, through the date of the public sale (as authorized under such documents and State law); and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="idc337c505-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2053/b/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> the amount realized at such sale.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idc337c506-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/105/368/tVI/s601/a">Pub. L. 105–368, title VI, § 601(a)</ref>, <date date="1998-11-11">Nov. 11, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/3344">112 Stat. 3344</ref>, § 3774; renumbered § 2053, <ref href="/us/pl/107/95/s5/d/1">Pub. L. 107–95, § 5(d)(1)</ref>, <date date="2001-12-21">Dec. 21, 2001</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/115/918">115 Stat. 918</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
